OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F427A1780938366
OL,3,CDouble jeopardy killer Billy Dunlop to
OL,4,Chave public parole hearing
OL,6,FTwo juries failed to reach a verdict
OL,7,Fbefore Dunlop was convicted of
OL,8,Fmurdering Ms Hogg.
OL,10,FMs Hogg's mother, Ann Ming, campaigned
OL,11,Ffor 15 years to have an 800-year-old
OL,12,Fdouble jeopardy law changed so Dunlop
OL,13,Fcould be charged for the same crime
OL,14,Ftwice, after he confessed and admitted
OL,15,Flying in court while in jail for
OL,16,Fanother crime.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/4
